    "updated_at": "2016-07-20T18:02:33Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The timer expects a MONOTONIC type because that is what is set during iomgr_init. It is now a common pattern in our codebase to convert the deadline to MONOTONIC when initing the timer. Otherwise an assertion is triggered in the grpc_timer_init code.\n\nWhen we use grpc_httpcli_get or post, the deadline is inherited from the credentials code and is of type REALTIME, and it will cause a problem (see #7131). Normal ssl handshake does not suffer from the problem because they pass in a deadline with the right time. See for example: https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/a9df5d1029b303a305481c4bb765c6bed2e8ebbb/src/core/ext/transport/chttp2/server/secure/server_secure_chttp2.c#L134 and https://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/b6163dfb4af3bf11df6cf3f051015ec3ee4a0f68/src/core/ext/client_config/subchannel.c#L392\n"
  },
